case_circumstances: On July 29, 2009, an employee of the South Bay International Wastewater Treatment Plant, a waste water treatment facility near the Tijuana River Valley area in San Ysidro, discovered the decedent's body on a conveyor belt.  Death was confirmed without medical intervention due to obviously fatal injuries and signs of decomposition.  In March 2010, The Office of the Attorney General in Baja got a hit on the decedent's fingerprints.  The subject had numerous aliases including Jose Angel Martinez Pineda, Jose Raul Martinez Pineda, Jose Ruben Castro Pineda, Raul Castro Perez, Jose Ruben Castro Perez, and Jose Angel Castro Pineda.  As of November 2013, officials in Mexico have been unable to confirm the decedent's identity or locate family.
